data.description: Auction Property. Auction Property. ONLINE AUCTION ONLY! In Cooperation with Alex Cooper Auctioneers. LIST PRICE IS OPENING BID AT THE ONLINE ONLY AUCTION.  Sale To Be Held On Auctioneer’s Website – Bidding begins Thursday, January 25, 2024 & ends Tuesday, January 30, 2024 @ 12:00 PM. Royal Highlands - Royal Highlands - RARE 4 bedroom floor plan with POOL! Built in 2020, this “almost new” one story home sits on .46 acres in a peaceful and quiet setting. The open floor plan features spacious and comfortable living spaces with a large center island connecting kitchen, great room, dining and flex areas so family and friends can enjoy each other’s company whether cooking, relaxing, entertaining or doing homework! The generously sized master bedroom includes an ensuite bath with dual sinks, stand up shower and large walk-in closet. In addition, there are 3 additional bedrooms and a second full bath. The laundry room is conveniently located between the 2 car attached garage and kitchen. Last, but not least, step outside to enjoy your 24x18, crystal clear, above ground pool with solar cover! Plenty of room for enjoying friends, grilling, gardening, even gazing in awe at the spectacular starry sky! You can’t do that in the city! There is a shed to store your kayaks, lawn equipment, or? No HOA, no CDD, no Deed Restrictions, no Flood (high and dry!), no water or sewer bills (because you have your own well and septic!) Also plenty of room to park your boat, RV, and big toys - which you can enjoy at all the recreational sites nearby! Boating… fishing… kayaking… swimming with the Manatees… Withlacoochee State Forest (Croom Motorcycle Area!)… Mermaids… Waterparks… so much to do and enjoy! Bonus details include new roof mounted, energy saving solar system (to be paid off at closing); energy star appliances; UV filter for the AC system; impact resistant windows; mini split AC unit for garage and full length sliding screens for the garage! All this and conveniently located as well – 10 minutes to shopping, groceries, great restaurants and schools - easy drive to greater Tampa and the airport to the south, Ocala to the north, top ranked beaches up and down the west coast, and Florida attractions to the east! What are you waiting for?!
